annotation.text:
The first mono LP release. Garrod & Lofthouse Ltd or Ernest. J.Day & Co front laminated cover, with large “mono” on front and with misspelled “You Really Gotta Hold On Me” title on the back side.
Black label with yellow logo and silver print. “The Parlophone Co. Ltd.” printed at the start perimeter print and “Recording first published 1963″ above side number. First pressing has misspelled “You Really Gotta Hold On Me” title and wrong “Jobete” publishing credit for “Money” (Side 2). 
Polythene-liner “Use Emitex” die-cut inner sleeve.
Matrix numbers: Side 1: XEX 447-1N; Side 2: XEX 448-1N.
